        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="481" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Defense Files: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-06">6 February
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To Secretary of State from Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_WJG1">Winant</persName> London serial number 2072.</p>
                <p>Soviet acting representative on the European Advisory Commission has informed me
                    that his government has approved the Protocol on zones of occupation and the
                    control machinery agreement for Germany. All 3 governments have now approved
                    without reservation the 3 basic documents for the control of Germany—the
                    instrument of unconditional surrender, the Protocol on zones of occupation and
                    the agreement on control machinery.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
